definition[0]: a very large strong bird with a beak like a hook that eats small animals, birds etc
definition[1]: two strokes less than par (=the usual number of strokes for a hole) in a game of golf
definition[2]: to use two strokes less than the usual number of strokes for a hole in a game of golf
definition[3]: a British weekly comic (=a magazine with stories told in pictures) for boys, which was popular in the 1950s and 1960s. Its best-known character was Dan Dare.
definition[4]: a US gold coin worth ten dollars
example[0]: Coin dealers have been loading up on American Eagle gold coins, a popular choice for small investors whenever they rush to buy gold.
